<!-- SECTION 7: 7-STEP PROCESS -->
<section class="steps-section" id="procedure-section">
    <div class="section-container">
        <header class="section-header" style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:48px;">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Our Process</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">8 Steps to DPIIT Startup Recognition</h2>
            <p class="section-subtitle" style="text-align:left;max-width:100%;">Patron's DPIIT pipeline runs from eligibility confirmation against the four eligible entity types (Pvt Ltd, LLP, registered Partnership Firm, Cooperative) under G.S.R. 108(E) 2026 through innovation and scalability documentation, pitch deck preparation, document compilation, Startup India portal registration, application submission, DPIIT Recognition Certificate issuance (7 to 14 days) and post-recognition benefit onboarding including GeM, SISFS, IPR rebates and the separate Section 80-IAC IMB filing where substance supports it.</p>
        </header>
        <div class="steps-container">
            <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-content">
                    <span class="step-badge">Step 1</span>
                    <h3 class="step-title">Eligibility Confirmation</h3>
                    <p>Verify entity type (Pvt Ltd / LLP / Partnership Firm / Cooperative under G.S.R. 108(E) 2026), age (under 10 years from incorporation) and turnover (under INR 200 crore in any preceding FY). Confirm NOT formed by splitting up or reconstruction of an existing business.</p>
                </div>
